{
	"info": {
		"_postman_id": "7f8b9e60-4c7b-4d40-8b1e-b83c50fe7dcd",
		"name": "ITI IRB Payment Integration",
		"description": "# ITI IRB Payment Integration API Documentation\n\nThis collection contains all the endpoints for the payment system in the ITI IRB project. It includes student endpoints for initiating checkouts, checking pending payments, payment history, receipts, and verifying transactions, as well as admin/manager endpoints for setting fees and viewing dashboards.\n\n### Authentication\n- All authenticated endpoints use **Sanctum Bearer Token** authentication.\n- Log in via the `/login` endpoint to automatically set the `token` variable in your environment/collection.\n\n### Environments\n- Import the provided Dev and Prod environment files.\n- Change `baseUrl` and `token` as needed.",
		"schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
	},
	"item": [
		{
			"name": "Authentication",
			"item": [
				{
					"name": "Login",
					"event": [
						{
							"listen": "test",
							"script": {
								"exec": [
									"var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
									"if (jsonData.status && jsonData.token) {",
									"    if (pm.environment.name) {",
									"        pm.environment.set(\"token\", jsonData.token);",
									"    }",
									"    pm.collectionVariables.set(\"token\", jsonData.token);",
									"    console.log(\"Token saved successfully!\");",
									"}"
								],
								"type": "text/javascript",
								"packages": {}
							}
						}
					],
					"request": {
						"auth": {
							"type": "noauth"
						},
						"method": "POST",
						"header": [
							{
								"key": "Content-Type",
								"value": "application/json",
								"type": "text"
							},
							{
								"key": "Accept",
								"value": "application/json",
								"type": "text"
							}
						],
						"body": {
							"mode": "raw",
							"raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"student@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"password\"\n}"
						},
						"url": {
							"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/login",
							"host": [
								"{{baseUrl}}"
							],
							"path": [
								"login"
							]
						},
						"description": "Authenticate user credentials. Saves the token dynamically upon a successful request.\n\n### Acceptable Fields:\n- `email` (string, required, valid email)\n- `password` (string, required)"
					},
					"response": [
